API_PKC Implementations for MAMBA-Frost

Subdirectories
- Reference_Implementation/
  ISO C reference implementation instances.
- Optimized_Implementation/
  Optimized implementation instances for 64-bit PC platforms.
- Additional_Implementation/
  Additional implementations (experimental, platform-specific, or future variants).

Instance layout expectations
- Each instance directory should be independently buildable with make.
- Typical flow per instance: make clean && make && make KAT && ./KAT_KEM.

Integration rules
- Official API_PKC files drng, auxfunc, and KAT_KEM should not be modified.
- Randomness is adapted through the official DRNG integration path.
- Hash/XOF adaptation is routed through auxfunc wrappers.

Note
- Frost was previously developed under the working name Venom.
